# BUSA Platform — Cursor Rules

## Project Overview
BUSA is a community platform for Uzbek students in Busan, Korea.
Next.js 14 App Router. TypeScript. Tailwind CSS. Static data now, GraphQL backend later.

## Design System
This project uses a Stitch-generated design. All components must match the existing design exactly.

### Colors — use these exact values, never deviate
primary: #00236f
primary-container: #1e3a8a
on-primary: #ffffff
on-primary-container: #90a8ff
primary-fixed-dim: #b6c4ff
on-primary-fixed-variant: #264191
secondary: #555d7e
surface: #f7f9fb
surface-container: #eceef0
surface-container-low: #f2f4f6
surface-container-high: #e6e8ea
surface-container-lowest: #ffffff
on-surface: #191c1e
on-surface-variant: #444651
outline-variant: #c5c5d3

### Fonts
font-headline: Space Grotesk — used for all headings
font-body: Inter — used for all body text
font-label: Inter — used for labels and small text
roboto font 

### Border radius
default: 0.25rem
lg: 0.5rem
xl: 0.75rem
2xl: 1rem
3xl: 1.5rem
full: 9999px

## Tech Stack
- Framework: Next.js 14 App Router
- Language: TypeScript — strict, no any types ever
- Styling: Tailwind CSS only — no inline styles, no CSS modules
- Animation: Framer Motion
- Forms: React Hook Form + Zod
- State: Zustand
- i18n: next-i18next (Uzbek + Russian)
- Images: Next.js Image component only — never raw img tags
- Icons: react-icons or Material Symbols Outlined

## Folder Structure
app/                    → routes only, nothing else
(public)/             → all public pages
(admin)/              → protected admin pages
components/
ui/                   → tiny reusable: Button, Card, Badge
layout/               → Navbar, Footer, PageWrapper
sections/             → full page sections
features/             → feature specific components
lib/
constants/            → routes.ts, static data
hooks/                → custom hooks
utils/                → helper functions
types/                → TypeScript interfaces

## Strict Rules — follow always

### Components
- Every component has TypeScript interface for props
- Named exports for components, default export at bottom
- 'use client' only when component uses useState, useEffect, onClick, or browser APIs
- Server Component by default — no 'use client' unless needed
- Never put logic inside page.tsx — use section components

### File naming
- Components: PascalCase → EventCard.tsx
- Hooks: camelCase → useFilter.ts
- Utils: camelCase → formatDate.ts
- Types: camelCase → event.ts
- Pages: lowercase → page.tsx

### TypeScript
- No 'any' type ever
- All props must have interfaces
- All API responses must have types in lib/types/
- Use 'as const' for constant objects

### Styling
- Tailwind only — no inline styles
- Use cn() utility from lib/utils/cn.ts for conditional classes
- Dark mode classes always included
- Mobile first — sm: md: lg: breakpoints
- Never hardcode colors — always use Tailwind color tokens from config

### Images
- Always use Next.js Image component
- Always provide alt text
- Always provide width and height
- Use fill prop for cover images

### Performance
- Every page section is a separate component
- Heavy components lazy loaded with dynamic()
- Images optimized with Next.js Image
- No useEffect for data that can be static

### Security
- No secrets in frontend code
- All env vars use NEXT_PUBLIC_ prefix
- Admin routes check auth before rendering
- No dangerouslySetInnerHTML ever

## Page Structure
Every page follows this pattern:
```typescript
// app/events/page.tsx
import EventsHero from '@/components/sections/EventsHero'
import EventsGrid from '@/components/sections/EventsGrid'

export default function EventsPage() {
  return (
    <>
      <EventsHero />
      <EventsGrid />
    </>
  )
}
```

## Component Pattern
Every component follows this exact pattern:
```typescript
// 1. Imports
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils/cn'

// 2. Types
interface EventCardProps {
  title: string
  date: string
  className?: string
}

// 3. Component
function EventCard({ title, date, className }: EventCardProps) {
  return (
    <div className={cn('rounded-xl bg-surface-container-lowest', className)}>
      <h3 className="font-headline text-primary">{title}</h3>
      <p className="font-body text-on-surface-variant">{date}</p>
    </div>
  )
}

// 4. Export
export default EventCard
```

## Static Data Pattern
Backend is not ready. Use static data from lib/constants/:
```typescript
// lib/constants/events.ts
import { Event } from '@/lib/types/event'

export const EVENTS: Event[] = [
  {
    id: '1',
    title: 'Navro\'z 2025',
    slug: 'navruz-2025',
    date: '2025-03-21',
    location: 'Busan PNUK',
    type: 'navruz',
    description: '...',
    coverPhoto: '/images/events/navruz-2025.jpg',
    photos: [],
    isUpcoming: false,
  }
]
```

## Routes
```typescript
// Always import from constants, never hardcode
import { ROUTES } from '@/lib/constants/routes'

// ROUTES object:
HOME: '/'
ABOUT: '/about'
EVENTS: '/events'
PROJECTS: '/projects'
GALLERY: '/gallery'
VISA: '/visa'
ARRIVE: '/arrive'
MY_SITUATION: '/my-situation'
ADMIN: '/admin'
```

