NEXT_PUBLIC_TELEGRAM_URL=https://t.me/busa_busan
NEXT_PUBLIC_INSTAGRAM_URL=https://instagram.com/busa_busan
NEXT_PUBLIC_SITE_NAME=BUSA

## Pages to Build
/ → Home (7 sections)
/about → Story + timeline + values + team
/projects → 4 project cards
/projects/[slug] → Project detail
/events → Events list + filter
/events/[slug] → Event detail
/gallery → Masonry photo grid
/arrive → Before arriving checklist
/my-situation → 3-step personal guide tool
/visa → Visa articles + type cards
/visa/[type] → D-2, D-10, E-7 detail
/visa/articles/[slug] → Single article
/admin → Content management

## Home Page Sections

Navbar — sticky, blur, BUSA logo + nav links + CTA button
HeroSection — fullscreen image, overlay, headline, 2 buttons
MarqueeSection — scrolling partner logos
WhatIsBusa — text left, image right
WhyBusa — asymmetric 4-card grid
ProjectsSection — bento grid 4 projects
StatsSection — blue card, 3 big numbers
Footer — 4 columns


## Stitch Design Reference
The original Stitch HTML design is the source of truth for:
- All visual design decisions
- Color usage
- Typography scale
- Spacing and layout
- Component structure
Convert Stitch HTML to Next.js components maintaining exact visual output.
When converting Stitch HTML:
1. Replace class with className
2. Replace img with Next.js Image
3. Replace href="#" with ROUTES constants
4. Replace hardcoded text with props or constants
5. Add TypeScript interfaces
6. Split large sections into smaller components
7. Add 'use client' only if interactive

